---
layout: base
title: Support The Freethinking Times
description: The Freethinking Times is funded entirely by readers — no ads, no sponsors, ever. Support the publication or individual authors directly.
permalink: /support/
---

{% set pubTipUrl = site.tipping.kofi or site.tipping.bmac or site.tipping.patreon %}
{% set authors_with_tipping = [] %}
{% for slug, a in authors %}
  {% if a.tipping and (a.tipping.kofi or a.tipping.bmac or a.tipping.patreon) %}
    {% set authors_with_tipping = (authors_with_tipping.push({slug: slug, name: a.name, url: a.tipping.kofi or a.tipping.bmac or a.tipping.patreon}), authors_with_tipping) %}
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}

<div class="container" style="padding-top: var(--space-10); padding-bottom: var(--space-20);">
  <div class="container--prose">

    <header style="margin-bottom: var(--space-10); padding-bottom: var(--space-6); border-bottom: 3px solid var(--color-ink);">
      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-masthead); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 3.815rem); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
        Reader-Funded. Always.
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-ink-muted); font-style: italic; max-width: 55ch; line-height: var(--leading-normal);">
        The Freethinking Times has no parent company, no institutional backer,
        and no advertising — not now, not ever. Every article you read here
        exists because readers chose to support it.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="article-body">

      <h2>How We're Funded</h2>

      <p>We accept no advertising, no sponsored content, no brand partnerships, and no funding from organizations with interests in our coverage areas. The Freethinking Times is supported entirely by readers — people who read what we publish and decide it's worth keeping alive.</p>

      <p>That's the whole model. No tiers, no paywalls, no members-only content. Everything published here is free to read. Reader support is not a transaction — it's a decision that independent, adversarial, intellectually serious journalism is worth existing in the world.</p>

      <h2>Where Your Support Goes</h2>

      <p>Support given to the publication goes directly toward the publication's future: the time required for investigative work, access to documents and databases, and the ability to pursue stories without worrying about whether they're commercially convenient. A small, consistent readership willing to contribute is what makes it possible to turn down anything that would compromise editorial independence.</p>

      <p>Support given directly to individual authors goes entirely to those authors. Authors manage their own reader support through their own accounts — the publication does not take a cut. If a piece of writing mattered to you and you want the person who wrote it to be able to write more, supporting them directly is the most efficient way to do that.</p>

      <h2>Two Ways to Support</h2>

    </div>

    {# ── Support options ── #}
    <div style="margin: var(--space-8) 0 var(--space-10);">

      {# Publication + Author blocks #}
      <div class="support-two-col">

        {# Publication support #}
        <div class="support-block">
          <div class="support-block__eyebrow">The Publication</div>
          <h3 class="support-block__heading">Support {{ site.title }}</h3>
          <p class="support-block__body">
            Contributions to the publication fund its ongoing work — investigative
            reporting, platform costs, and the editorial independence to pursue
            stories on their own terms. No portion goes to individual authors;
            this is the publication's operating fund.
          </p>
          {% if pubTipUrl %}
          <div class="support-block__actions">
            <a class="tip-badge tip-badge--pub"
               href="{{ pubTipUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
               data-tippy-content="Support {{ site.title }}. Reader contributions keep us independent, ad-free, and able to pay our contributors fairly."
               data-tippy-theme="badge" data-tippy-placement="top">
              <span class="tip-badge__label">support</span><span class="tip-badge__value">{{ site.shortTitle or site.title }}</span>
            </a>
            <a class="support-block__learn" href="/transparency/">How we operate &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          {% endif %}
        </div>

        {# Author support #}
        <div class="support-block">
          <div class="support-block__eyebrow">Individual Authors</div>
          <h3 class="support-block__heading">Support a Contributor</h3>
          <p class="support-block__body">
            Authors who accept reader support do so through their own accounts.
            The publication receives nothing from author tips — 100% goes directly
            to the writer. Look for the support badge on any article byline or
            author page.
          </p>
          {% if authors_with_tipping.length %}
          <div class="support-block__author-list">
            {% for a in authors_with_tipping %}
            <a class="tip-badge"
               href="{{ a.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
               data-tippy-content="Support {{ a.name }} directly. Your tip goes entirely to the author."
               data-tippy-theme="badge" data-tippy-placement="top">
              <span class="tip-badge__label">support</span><span class="tip-badge__value">{{ a.name }}</span>
            </a>
            {% endfor %}
          </div>
          {% endif %}
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

    <hr style="margin-bottom: var(--space-10);">

    {# Email subscribe #}
    <div style="margin-bottom: var(--space-10);">
      <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-headline); font-size: var(--text-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
        No budget right now? Subscribe instead.
      </h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-ink-muted); font-size: var(--text-base); max-width: 55ch; margin-bottom: var(--space-6); line-height: var(--leading-normal);">
        A larger readership makes this publication more visible and more sustainable.
        Subscribing by email is free and genuinely useful.
      </p>
      {% set subscribeVariant = "inline" %}
      {% include "partials/subscribe.njk" %}
    </div>

    <hr style="margin-bottom: var(--space-10);">

    <div class="article-body">
      <h2>Other ways to help</h2>

      <p><strong>Share specific pieces.</strong> When an article is worth reading, send it to one person who would find it genuinely useful. Not broadcast — targeted. A good article landing in front of the right reader is worth more than a hundred passive impressions.</p>

      <p><strong>Link to us.</strong> If you write, blog, or maintain any kind of online presence, linking to pieces you found valuable is how independent publications build the search presence that brings new readers.</p>

      <p><strong>Write a letter.</strong> Reader correspondence published in the Letters section is part of the publication's editorial content. A thoughtful response to something we've published contributes to the work directly. <a href="/letters/submit/">Write a letter</a>.</p>

      <p><strong>Tell us what we're missing.</strong> The best editorial tip is a story that matters and isn't being told. If you know of something that deserves investigation, <a href="/tips/">send us a tip</a>.</p>
    </div>

    {# Closing note #}
    <div style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule); padding-top: var(--space-8); margin-top: var(--space-10);">
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink-faint); font-style: italic;">
        The Freethinking Times does not accept advertising, sponsored content, affiliate fees,
        or funding from organizations with interests in our coverage areas. Reader support
        is the only kind we take. Individual authors process their own support independently;
        the publication does not take a percentage.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
